From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Skinstad Drabitzius <daniel.drabitzius@northern.tech>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] vexpress: drop the second DRAM bank when it is unpopulated

vexpress declares two DRAM banks, but the second (PHYS_SDRAM_2, 0x80000000) is
not always populated. get_ram_size() sizes a bank by writing to its cells and
reading them back; an empty cell reads back 0, so it cannot tell an empty cell
from one holding 0, and sizes an empty bank as a few bytes instead of 0. A bank
is then registered for memory that is not there. Since the EFI memory map became
LMB-backed (v2025.01) that bank reaches the kernel and hangs it in early boot.
Drop a bank whose probed size is below 4 KB: it cannot be real DRAM, while a
partially-populated bank keeps its true size.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Mender specific]

Signed-off-by: Daniel Skinstad Drabitzius <daniel.drabitzius@northern.tech>
---
 board/armltd/vexpress/vexpress_common.c | 13 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

--- a/board/armltd/vexpress/vexpress_common.c
+++ b/board/armltd/vexpress/vexpress_common.c
@@ -16,6 +16,7 @@
  * Philippe Robin, <philippe.robin@arm.com>
  */
 #include <config.h>
+#include <linux/sizes.h>
 #include <bootstage.h>
 #include <cpu_func.h>
 #include <init.h>
@@ -86,6 +87,18 @@
 	gd->bd->bi_dram[1].size =
 			get_ram_size((long *)PHYS_SDRAM_2, PHYS_SDRAM_2_SIZE);
 
+	/*
+	 * The second DRAM bank is not always populated. get_ram_size()
+	 * sizes a bank by writing to cells and reading them back; an empty
+	 * cell reads back 0, so it cannot tell empty from a cell holding 0
+	 * and sizes an empty bank as a few bytes, not 0. Drop a bank below
+	 * 4 KB: it cannot be real DRAM; a real or partial bank is unaffected.
+	 */
+	if (gd->bd->bi_dram[1].size < SZ_4K) {
+		gd->bd->bi_dram[1].start = 0;
+		gd->bd->bi_dram[1].size = 0;
+	}
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
